  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to determine whether modules of Metacognitive Training: Jumping
      to Conclusions and To empathize... are effective in the treatment of patients with
      schizophrenia. Also it was investigated whether these modules have specific impact on
      cognitive biases severity.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Investigators employ randomized controlled trial design. Patients in ward were recruited for
      the study in three waves. In each wave patients were assessed pre-intervention, then randomly
      allocated in one of three groups: with modules of Metacognitive Training or control group.
      Then patients were assessed post-intervention.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
